(2. Backend validates credentials and role, returns token + profile.) Tj
T*
(3. Frontend stores token/profile in localStorage.) Tj
T*
(4. Subsequent Axios calls include Bearer token via interceptor.) Tj
T*
T*
(5.2 Team member task flow) Tj
T*
(1. TaskManager GET /api/workspace/tasks?assignedTo=<name>&filters.) Tj
T*
(2. Backend filters, paginates, returns data + meta.) Tj
T*
(3. User toggles task -> PATCH /api/workspace/tasks/:id/toggle.) Tj
T*
(4. Backend updates task.done and writes activity log.) Tj
T*
(5. Frontend refreshes list.) Tj
T*
T*
(5.3 Management assignment flow) Tj
T*
(1. Manager creates member/task via management UI.) Tj
T*
(2. Backend persists changes and activity log entries.) Tj
T*
(3. Team member sees assigned tasks filtered by own name.) Tj
T*
T*
(5.4 Chat flow) Tj
T*
(1. Client loads recent messages using GET /api/workspace/messages.) Tj
T*
(2. New message POST /api/workspace/messages.) Tj
T*
(3. Backend appends message and audit record.) Tj
T*
(4. Updated messages are returned for immediate UI sync.) Tj
T*
T*
(6\) Security and Reliability Notes) Tj
T*
(Current strengths:) Tj
T*
(- JWT-based stateless authentication.) Tj
T*
(- Role-based route protection for privileged operations.) Tj
T*
(- Password hashing with bcrypt.) Tj
T*
(- Server-side validation on critical fields and enums.) Tj
T*
(- Structured error responses and health endpoint.) Tj
T*
T*
(Important gaps to address for production:) Tj
T*
(- JWT secret defaults to hardcoded fallback; must be environment-only in production.) Tj
T*
(- Tokens are kept in localStorage \(XSS exposure risk\). Consider secure HttpOnly cookies.) Tj
T*
(- CORS is localhost-only; production environment whitelist/configuration is needed.) Tj
T*
(- No rate limiting/brute-force protection on login.) Tj
T*
(- No centralized schema validation layer \(e.g., zod/joi\) for all payloads.) Tj
T*
(- No refresh-token strategy or session revocation.) Tj
T*
(- Management page still uses prompt\(\) for edits/comments \(UX and audit limitations\).) Tj
T*
T*
(7\) Scalability Considerations) Tj
T*
(- Split workspace aggregate into separate collections when task/message volume grows.) Tj
T*
(- Add indexes for frequent filters \(assignedTo, priority, done, createdAt\).) Tj
T*
(- Introduce websocket layer for chat and realtime board updates.) Tj
T*
(- Add optimistic UI updates with rollback on failure for better responsiveness.) Tj
T*
(- Move from polling/refetch-after-write to event-driven invalidation.) Tj
T*
T*
ET
endstream
